1.2  Value Proposition Map
The Value Proposition Canvas of Osterwalder, Pigneur, Bernarda and Smith (2014) was applied to the primary customer segment, an anonymized Lebanese polymer-compounding firm operating a pilot facility in the Mount Lebanon region, with secondary buyer archetypes, regional asphalt contractors, MENA thermoplastic compounders, and sports-surfacing installers, addressed separately in the market analysis of Chapter II. The Canvas separates the customer profile (jobs, pains, gains) from the value map (pain relievers, gain creators), and the venture-design discipline consists of demonstrating fit between the two sides through specific, measurable design choices rather than through abstract value claims.
