1.4  Business Model v1.0 (Canvas)
The Business Model Canvas (Osterwalder & Pigneur, 2010) was applied at the version-one level of specification to capture the venture's go-to-market design at Phase 1 launch. The nine canvas blocks are summarised in Table 1.4 and elaborated in the narrative that follows. The v1.0 specification is deliberately conservative: it commits to the anchor-customer relationship as the foundation of Phase 1 revenue while preserving optionality on secondary buyers, on Phase 2 rubberised-asphalt offtake, and on Phase 3 co-formulation activity. The v2.0 Canvas of Chapter III absorbs the market evidence of Chapter II and refines several blocks, most notably Customer Segments (with the Tier-2 diversification layer formalised), Revenue Streams (with the steel-by-product offset made explicit), and Key Partnerships (with the IDAL Investment Promotion Zone Class B incentive added).
