The CAPEX range is driven primarily by the choice between new-condition and quality-refurbished equipment and by the size of the solar photovoltaic installation. Phase 1 is scoped to the refurbished-equipment configuration combined with a 100 kWp solar installation, yielding a target equipment CAPEX of approximately USD 250,000. A Phase 1A minimum-viable configuration that defers the granulator and runs the line at coarser fractions only is feasible at approximately USD 150,000 and is retained as a contingency in case grant funding disburses slower than planned.
5.3  Suppliers and Partners
The supplier-and-partner architecture is built across four tiers: feedstock suppliers (upstream), processing inputs (imported), logistics and service partners, and ecosystem partners. For equipment, ouli china s the primary supplier for the machines : …. Feedstock collection draws on a network of approximately 60 tire-shop nodes in Keserwan and Matn under formal supply contracts, plus the municipalities of Jounieh, Antelias and Bikfaya for cluster pickup arrangements.
Logistics partners include local owner-operator flatbed contractors at USD 25 to 45 per tonne for inbound tire delivery, with multiple contractors qualified to ensure redundancy. Steel offtake partners are Lebanon Steel of Sin El Fil and MASCO. Insurance is led by Bankers Assurance with Allianz SNA providing liability and environmental impairment cover, AROPE providing cargo and transport cover, and Chedid Capital Insurance Brokers acting as the placing broker. Legal counsel is provided by a Beirut law firm with industrial-environmental specialty practice.
